# Lattice Design System Rules

This project follows the **Kognitos Lattice Design System** (`@kognitos/lattice`).
Even though the frontend is vanilla HTML/JS (not React), we adopt Lattice's design tokens, color system, and styling philosophy to maintain visual consistency with other Kognitos products.

## Core Philosophy

> **Use semantic tokens, not hardcoded values.**

- ❌ NEVER use hardcoded hex/rgb colors (e.g. `#4f46e5`, `rgb(79,70,229)`)
- ❌ NEVER use Tailwind arbitrary color values (e.g. `bg-[#ff0000]`)
- ❌ NEVER use inline `style="..."` for colors, fonts, or spacing
- ✅ USE CSS custom properties defined in `<style>` via `var(--token)`
- ✅ USE Tailwind utility classes that reference semantic tokens
- ✅ USE the semantic color classes defined in the project's CSS

## Color Tokens (from Lattice theme.css)

The project defines CSS custom properties on `:root` matching Lattice's token system.
Always use these — they support future light/dark theme switching.

### Semantic Colors

| Token                    | Purpose                           |
|--------------------------|-----------------------------------|
| `--primary`              | Primary brand actions / highlights |
| `--primary-foreground`   | Text on primary backgrounds        |
| `--secondary`            | Less prominent elements            |
| `--secondary-foreground` | Text on secondary backgrounds      |
| `--accent`               | Accent highlights                  |
| `--accent-foreground`    | Text on accent backgrounds         |
| `--background`           | Page background                    |
| `--foreground`           | Default text color                 |
| `--card`                 | Card backgrounds                   |
| `--card-foreground`      | Card text                          |
| `--muted`                | Muted / subdued backgrounds        |
| `--muted-foreground`     | Subdued text (metadata, hints)     |
| `--destructive`          | Error / danger states              |
| `--border`               | Default borders                    |
| `--input`                | Input borders                      |
| `--ring`                 | Focus rings                        |
| `--brand`                | Kognitos brand color               |

### Status Colors

Each status color has a full numeric scale (50–900) for backgrounds, text, and borders:

| Token family     | Purpose                  | Scale classes                                       |
|------------------|--------------------------|-----------------------------------------------------|
| `destructive-*`  | Error / danger states    | `bg-destructive-50` … `bg-destructive-900`, etc.    |
| `success-*`      | Success / positive       | `bg-success-50` … `bg-success-900`, etc.            |
| `warning-*`      | Warning / caution        | `bg-warning-50` … `bg-warning-900`, etc.            |
| `informative-*`  | Informational / neutral  | `bg-informative-50` … `bg-informative-900`, etc.    |

Additional tokens:

| Token                      | Purpose               |
|----------------------------|-----------------------|
| `--success-foreground`     | Text on success bg    |
| `--warning-foreground`     | Text on warning bg    |
| `--informative-foreground` | Text on info bg       |
| `--link`                   | Link text color       |
| `--code-bg`                | Code block background |
| `--code-fg`                | Code block text       |

### Sidebar Colors

| Token                           | Purpose                        |
|---------------------------------|--------------------------------|
| `--sidebar`                     | Sidebar background             |
| `--sidebar-foreground`          | Sidebar text                   |
| `--sidebar-primary`             | Sidebar active / selected      |
| `--sidebar-primary-foreground`  | Text on sidebar primary bg     |
| `--sidebar-accent`              | Sidebar hover / accent         |
| `--sidebar-accent-foreground`   | Text on sidebar accent bg      |
| `--sidebar-border`              | Sidebar borders                |
| `--sidebar-muted`               | Sidebar muted text             |

## Tailwind Integration

When using Tailwind classes in HTML, reference design tokens through the custom CSS classes:

```css
/* Good — semantic token classes */
.bg-primary    { background: var(--primary); }
.text-fg       { color: var(--foreground); }
.border-border { border-color: var(--border); }

/* Bad — hardcoded arbitrary values */
.bg-[#4f46e5]  /* ❌ Never */
```

## Typography

- **Font family**: `PP Neue Montreal, sans-serif` (Lattice default) — fallback to system sans-serif
- Use Tailwind `text-sm`, `text-xs`, `text-base`, `text-lg` for sizing
- Use `font-medium`, `font-semibold`, `font-bold` for weights
- Headings should use `font-semibold` or `font-bold`

## Component Patterns

When building UI elements, follow these patterns:

1. **Cards**: Use `bg-card text-card-foreground border border-border rounded-xl` — never custom card colors
2. **Buttons**: Primary = `bg-primary text-primary-foreground`, Secondary = `bg-secondary text-secondary-foreground`
3. **Inputs**: Use `border-input rounded-lg focus:ring-2 focus:ring-ring` for consistent focus states
4. **Badges**: Use status token scales — `success-*` (green), `warning-*` (amber), `destructive-*` (red), `informative-*` (blue)
5. **Empty states**: Center content with muted icon + muted-foreground text
6. **Sidebar nav**: Use sidebar tokens for background, hover states, and active indicators

## Spacing & Layout

- Use Tailwind spacing scale: `p-4`, `gap-3`, `mb-6` etc.
- Standard card padding: `p-4` or `p-5`
- Section spacing: `space-y-5` or `space-y-6`
- Border radius: `rounded-lg` for inputs, `rounded-xl` for cards/panels

## Accessibility

- All interactive elements need visible focus states (`focus:ring-2 focus:ring-ring`)
- Use semantic HTML (`<button>`, `<nav>`, `<main>`, `<aside>`)
- Include `aria-label` for icon-only buttons
- Ensure sufficient color contrast between foreground/background pairs

## Dark Mode Readiness

Even if dark mode is not yet implemented, structure CSS to be dark-mode ready:
- All colors defined as CSS custom properties on `:root`
- A `.dark` class on the root element can override all tokens
- Never use colors that only work in light mode
